fields.description:
Upgrading to the latest version of Bamboo 4.3 from an older version of 4.x that was running on WAR installation resulted in an NPE while bootstrapping. The following appears in the logs
{code}
2012-11-04 19:26:18.224002500 java.lang.NullPointerException
2012-11-04 19:26:18.224003500 at com.atlassian.bamboo.setup.DefaultBootstrapManager.performPersistenceUpgrade(DefaultBootstrapManager.java:258)
2012-11-04 19:26:18.224004500 at com.atlassian.config.bootstrap.DefaultAtlassianBootstrapManager.init(DefaultAtlassianBootstrapManager.java:80)
2012-11-04 19:26:18.224019500 at com.atlassian.bamboo.setup.BootstrapLoaderListener.contextInitialized(BootstrapLoaderListener.java:67)
2012-11-04 19:26:18.224020500 at org.apache.catalina.core.StandardContext.listenerStart(StandardContext.java:4205)
{code}

*Workaround*
Add the corresponding driver class to the {{HOME/bamboo.cfg.xml}} file as it was missing. Here is a sample for the different databases:

MYSQL:
{code}
<property name="hibernate.connection.driver_class">com.mysql.jdbc.Driver</property>
{code}

PostgreSQL:
{code}
<property name="hibernate.connection.driver_class">org.postgresql.Driver</property>
{code}

ORACLE:
{code}
<property name="hibernate.connection.driver_class">oracle.jdbc.driver.OracleDriver</property>
{code}

MSSQL:
{code}
<property name="hibernate.connection.driver_class">net.sourceforge.jtds.jdbc.Driver</property>
{code}

{quote}
This does not appear to work when selecting key without passphrase  (same with ssh task).

A workaround appears to be:  set with bogus passphrase, save, change to without passphrase, save
{quote}

From Atlassian Answers:

{quote}
Is it possible to deploy a WAR file named like "my-project-*.war" using the tomcat plugin?

This is because the WAR file was packaged in other job, and the resulted WAR is shared using "shared artifacts". Is this procedure correct or common?

I can change de final name to exclude de version number (the wildcard is used to match this version number), but I prefer this name because the file is also copied using SCP.
{quote}

Currently, if the P4 Server is set to use UTF8, the following variable needs to be setup locally in the Server and Remote Agents:
{code}
P4CHARSET=utf8
{code}

Allowing the settings to be added via the UI would make things much easier.

(ie. Fisheye already has an UI option for this)
